President Obama issued a statement expressing the United States' commitment to bringing those responsible for harming Americans to justice. He authorized an operation in Libya to detain Ahmed Abu Khatallah, who was charged for his role in the attacks on the U.S. facilities in Benghazi. The President praised the efforts of the military, law enforcement, and intelligence personnel involved in apprehending Khatallah, stating that he will now face the American justice system. The statement also recognized the four Americans who lost their lives in Benghazi and expressed gratitude for their service. The United States will continue its efforts to bring justice to those responsible for the Benghazi attacks and remain vigilant against terrorism. The President also emphasized the support for the Libyan people in their pursuit of a peaceful, prosperous, and democratic society.